{
  "text": "From June 1973 to January 1978, it was our policy at the Johannesburg Hospital to use the Bj'ork-Shiley prosthesis for mitral valve replacement. During this period a total of 224 white patients were discharged from hospital after Bj'ork-Shiley mitral valve replacement. Follow-up data for 100% of these hospital survivors were obtained until the study was closed on March 31, 1978 . At that time [CITATION_1] patients had died, one of whom was examined by us and is the first of the 12 patients in this series of thrombosed Bj'ork-Shiley mitral prostheses. Information on the other 18 deaths was obtained from the records of this and other hospitals, necropsy reports and telephone conversations with physicians or relatives.",
